# ~/.skill-source-ignore example -- single-host ignore list
#
# List skill names that are "permanently used on only one end, not to be adopted into the source", one per line.
# scan.sh folds them out of "adoption candidates" into a single CANDIDATE_IGNORED line,
# so reconcile no longer spams these fixed-noise entries line by line.
#
# Typically ignored:
#   - plugin-supplied skills (source lives in their GitHub repo, path is versioned, can't be symlink-merged)
#   - skills that collide with the other end's builtin and are bound to stay single-host
#
# Usage: copy this file to ~/.skill-source-ignore and fill it in as needed
#   cp single-host.example ~/.skill-source-ignore
# Or put it elsewhere and point at it via an env var:
#   SYNC_IGNORE=/your/path  scan.sh
#
# Rules:
#   - one skill name per line (exact match, case-sensitive)
#   - lines starting with "#", or content after an inline "#", are comments
#   - blank lines are ignored
#
# Note: this is a template and contains no real entries. Your list lives in ~/.skill-source-ignore,
#       which is in your home dir and naturally does not travel with the skill repo, so private
#       skill names are never committed to a public repo.
#
# Example (remove the "#" below and replace with your own skill names):
# my-local-only-skill
# some-plugin-supplied-skill
